parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank and Crossover Pipe Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank and crossover pipe can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and environmental damage. The strong odor of gasoline can also cause discomfort and health issues for the occupants.
symptoms: Strong fuel odor inside the vehicle
fuel leaks
fuel puddles under the vehicle
difficulty filling the tank
fuel gauge malfunctions
and fuel pump failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank leak/crossover tube failure can cause fuel to leak onto the exhaust system, creating a fire hazard, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Strong fuel smell
fuel leaking from the left fuel tank
fuel dripping onto the garage floor
fuel smell in the car
gas smell when parked
fuel leak when the engine is running
fuel leak when the tank is full
fuel leak when the tank is over half full.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column lock can cause the steering wheel to lock up, making it difficult or impossible to steer, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel locks up
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the "Service Steering Column" message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the active handling system can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The "Service Active Handling System" message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle pulls to one side
the brakes lock up
the vehicle jerks or lunges.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal can cause the pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak can cause a fire hazard, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: A visible gasoline leak
a strong gasoline odor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seatbelt can fail to restrain the occupant in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seatbelt does not lock
the seatbelt unlocks while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty airbag system can fail to deploy in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag system cannot be checked for effectiveness.
